> The famous grilled meat bento machine featured on TV.

Finally, hidden in the city of Kagoshima, on the southwestern tip of the
island of Kyushu, lies a fresh crepe vending machine. It's located in
Kagoshima's [Tenmonkan](https://youtu.be/89AfXJNRNaQ) shopping district,
hidden near a bus stop and reportedly difficult to find.

Those lucky enough to find this most unusual of vending machines are treated
to tasty crepes at the cost of 200 yen (about US$ 2).

> 鹿児島の隠れた名物クレープの自販機！ [pic.twitter.com/eBocQVwotU](https://t.co/eBocQVwotU)
>
> — やきとり弁当 (@kirakira2nd) [August 24,
> 2018](https://twitter.com/kirakira2nd/status/1032895740702388229?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw)

> Kagoshima's hidden gem: a crepe vending machine!

The vending machine serves a variety of flavors of crepe, including chocolate
cream, caramel, strawberry cream, and cheese. The crepes are delivered in a
glass bottle, which customers are asked to return after they are done.

With this machine being a one-of-a-kind favorite, some users are wondering if
other cities also have one of their own:

> ないです･･･  
>  いいなぁ！！
